data.value: Trinity College, officially the College of the Holy and Undivided Trinity of Queen Elizabeth near Dublin, is the only compound college of the University of Dublin, a research university located in Dublin, Ireland. The college was founded in 1592 as the "mother" of a new university,modelled after the universities of Oxford and Cambridge, but, unlike these other ancient universities, only one college was ever established; as such, the names "Trinity College" and "University of Dublin" are usually synonymous for practical purposes. It is one of the seven ancient universities of Britain and Ireland, as well as Ireland's oldest university.
